Url%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22We%20are%202%20brothers%20who%20left%20corporate%20jobs%20to%20start%20our%20own%20sneaker%20company.%20Here's%20how%20we%20found%20our%20niche%20in%20a%20market%20dominated%20by%20big%20brands.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brandon%20and%20Josh%20Brubaker.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a36362dcdb354a9857777c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBrandon%20and%20Josh%20Brubaker%2C%20co-founders%20of%20Clearweather%20Footwear.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Clearweather.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20years%20in%20the%20industry%2C%20brothers%20Brandon%20and%20Josh%20Brubaker%20co-founded%20Clearweather%20Footwear.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20brothers%20from%20California%20are%20both%20designers%20and%20run%20their%20company%20with%20three%20other%20employees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20create%20skateboarding%20and%20lifestyle%20shoes%20and%20hope%20to%20leave%20the%20company%20to%20their%20kids%20someday.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Brandon%20and%20Josh%20Brubaker%2C%20who%20cofounded%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclearweatherbrand.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EClearweather%20Footwear%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20in%202014.%20The%20brothers%2C%20ages%2050%20and%2041%2C%20respectively%2C%20have%20nearly%2050%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20the%20footwear%20industry%20between%20them%2C%20working%20at%20Vans%2C%20Converse%2C%20Supra%20Footwear%2C%20and%20Quiksilver%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJosh%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThere's%20an%20old%20saying%20in%20footwear%20where%20you%20say%20to%20yourself%2C%20'%26quot%3BI%20really%20like%20this%20shoe.%20I%20don't%20know%20why.%26quot%3B%20That%20just%20means%20it%20was%20developed%20correctly%20and%20that%20all%20the%20elements%20are%20where%20they're%20supposed%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBrandon%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe're%20definitely%20meticulous%20about%20that.%20A%20line%20could%20be%20off%20by%20a%20couple%20of%20millimeters%20and%20it%20throws%20off%20the%20whole%20shoe%2C%20right%3F%20We%20want%20to%20be%20in%20control%20of%20everything%20from%20the%20designs%20to%20the%20look%20and%20feel%20and%20what%20they%20represent%20when%20they%20come%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJosh%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20other%20hard%20part%20is%20making%20something%20feel%20familiar%20yet%20different%20without%20copying%20it.%20I%20think%20that's%20something%20that%20we're%20both%20really%20good%20at%2C%20and%20it%20took%20years%20of%20getting%20there%2C%20of%20going%20overboard%20with%20lines%20and%20then%20trying%20to%20remove%20lines%2C%20and%20place%20them%20strategically.%20We're%20not%20inventing%20anything.%20We're%20just%20trying%20to%20be%20clever%20and%20do%20our%20craft%20the%20way%20we%20learned%20to%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBrandon%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20had%20always%20drawn%20as%20a%20kid%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20really%20take%20it%20seriously.%20In%20college%2C%20a%20friend%20of%20mine%20connected%20with%20an%20owner%20at%20Vans%2C%20who%20asked%20if%20my%20friend%20knew%20anybody%20who%20could%20draw.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20drew%20a%20skate%20shoe%20and%20a%20snowboard%20boot%2C%20and%20I%20faxed%20it%20to%20him.%20The%20first%20guy%20I%20interviewed%20with%20wanted%20me%20to%20get%20his%20coffee%20and%20be%20his%20gopher%2C%20which%20sounded%20ridiculous%20to%20me.%20Later%2C%20the%20head%20of%20design%20got%20ahold%20of%20my%20drawing%2C%20called%20me%2C%20and%20asked%20me%20to%20come%20back%20and%20interview%20properly.%20When%20I%20did%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20hire%20you.%20You%20can%20still%20go%20to%20school%2C%20but%20I%20want%20to%20give%20you%20a%20position%20as%20a%20junior%20designer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20jaw%20hit%20the%20floor.%20I%20took%20the%20job%2C%20and%20about%20five%20months%20later%2C%20they%20offered%20me%20a%20full-time%20position.%20The%20amount%20of%20money%20that%20they%20were%20going%20to%20pay%20me%20to%20draw%20shoes%2C%20I%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20best%20thing%20that's%20ever%20happened%20to%20me.%26quot%3B%20And%20I%20just%20ran%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ended%20up%20working%20at%20Vans%20for%20eight%20years%2C%20worked%20my%20way%20up%20through%20the%20design%20team%2C%20and%20ended%20up%20working%20on%20almost%20all%20the%20signature%20shoes%20that%20were%20developed%20during%20that%20time%20and%20working%20with%20skateboarders%20I%20admired%20growing%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJosh%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFor%20me%2C%20being%20his%20younger%20brother%2C%20I%20would%20always%20ride%20his%20coattails.%20Skateboarding%20was%20my%20first%20love%2C%20and%20I%20always%20liked%20to%20draw.%20I%20didn't%20even%20put%20two%20and%20two%20together%20that%20humans%20drew%20shoes%20until%20he%20got%20the%20job%20at%20Vans.%20I%20was%20in%20seventh%20grade%2C%20and%20I%20got%20to%20go%20in%20and%20see%20how%20everything%20worked.%20It%20was%20just%20inspiring.%20It%20opened%20up%20a%20whole%20new%20thought%20process%20of%20what%20I%20could%20do%20with%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBrandon%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20He%20became%20a%20wear-tester%20for%20Vans%20because%20he%20was%20the%20sample%20size.%20He%20would%20walk%20around%20with%20signature%20skate%20shoes%20that%20even%20the%20skaters%20didn't%20have%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJosh%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFrom%20seventh%20grade%20onward%2C%20I%20drew%20shoes%20every%20night%20until%20I%20got%20my%20first%20job%20at%20Quiksilver.%20I%20have%20a%20big%20group%20of%20friends%20that%20I%20grew%20up%20skating%20with%2C%20and%20they%20all%20knew%20what%20Brandon%20was%20doing%20because%20he's%20my%20older%20brother.%20They%20call%20him%20the%20Godfather%20because%20he%20basically%20got%20us%20all%20into%20the%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20we're%20the%20type%20of%20people%20who%20want%20to%20put%20our%20friends%20on%2C%20not%20just%20because%20they're%20our%20friends%2C%20but%20because%20they're%20talented.%20You%20want%20to%20work%20with%20good%20company%20and%20people%20that%20you%20trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBrandon%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ENobody%20gets%20the%20layup.%20You%20have%20to%20be%20damn%20near%20the%20best%20at%20what%20you%20do%20for%20me%20and%20Josh%20to%20vouch%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJosh%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThere's%20a%20reason%20why%20you%20could%20probably%20count%20the%20major%20footwear%20brands%20on%20one%20hand.%20It's%20a%20heritage%20industry%20ruled%20by%20money%20and%20power%2C%20the%20brands%20within%20the%20sneaker%20world%20especially.%20The%20times%20have%20changed.%20When%20we%20were%20growing%20up%2C%20we%20always%20were%20looking%20for%20things%20that%20people%20didn't%20have.%20You%20wanted%20to%20be%20the%20only%20one%20with%20these%20shoes.%20Well%2C%20it's%20totally%20flipped%20upside%20down%2C%20and%20now%20everyone%20wants%20what%20everyone%20else%20has.%20So%20that%20just%20is%20more%20ammo%20for%20the%20majors.%20The%20Nike%2C%20the%20Adidas%2C%20the%20Yeezy%2C%20the%20New%20Balance%2C%20the%20Converse.%20That's%20their%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20a%20young%20brand%20and%20trying%20to%20compete%20with%20them%20is%20really%20difficult%20because%20people%20aren't%20buying%20the%20design%20because%20of%20the%20design.%20They're%20buying%20it%20because%20of%20the%20brand%20and%20because%20everyone%20else%20has%20it.%20It's%20been%20an%20upward%20battle%2C%20and%20that's%20why%20we're%20trying%20to%20scale%20back%20into%20our%20true%20roots%2C%20which%20is%20skateboarding.%20We've%20already%20laid%20the%20foundation%20of%20who%20we%20are%3A%20We%20are%20going%20to%20be%20the%20luxury%20skate%20brand%20that%20also%20makes%