%2Fwent-on-trip-with-friend-break-from-kids-refreshed-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E've%20never%20been%20away%20from%20them%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20than%20two%20nights.%20And%20those%20infrequent%20two-night%20mini-getaways%20have%20been%20with%20my%20husband.%20So%2C%20in%2010%20years%2C%20I've%20never%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsafety-tips-from-female-solo-traveler-all-50-states%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraveled%20alone%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-solo-travel-destinations-in-us-from-frequent-traveler-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraveling%20solo%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20never%20been%20something%20I%20craved.%20I%20love%20going%20away%20as%20a%20family%2C%20stressful%20although%20it%20may%20be%20at%20times.%20Paddling%20in%20the%20ocean%20amid%20their%20screams%20when%20the%20cold%20water%20touches%20their%20feet.%20Searching%20for%20a%20shop%20that%20sells%20ice%20cream.%20Movie%20marathons%20when%20it's%20raining.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20a%20childhood%20friend%20of%20mine%20got%20in%20touch%20to%20invite%20me%20to%20her%20wedding%20in%20Richmond%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-things-living-in-virginia-from-someone-who-left-misses-it-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVirginia%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20first%2C%20I%20replied%20I%20couldn't%20make%20it.%20The%20cost%20of%20traveling%20from%20the%20UK%20to%20a%20small%20airport%20in%20Richmond%20was%20far%20too%20expensive%20for%20a%20short%20trip%2C%20and%20I%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20find%20someone%20to%20have%20the%20kids%20with%20while%20I%20was%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20behind%20my%20response%20was%20not%20just%20logical%20reasoning%20but%20fear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20was%20afraid%20that%20something%20would%20happen%20to%20me%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20scared%20of%20travel%20after%20not%20having%20been%20on%20a%20plane%20in%20seven%20years.%20Petrified%20of%20dying%20and%20leaving%20my%20children%20behind.%20Worried%20about%20the%20budget%20repercussions%20of%20spending%20money%20on%20a%20trip%20that%20only%20I%20would%20enjoy.%20Nervous%20that%20something%20would%20go%20wrong%20with%20my%20visa%20and%20that%20I%20would%20be%20prohibited%20from%20re-entering%20the%20UK.%20Some%20of%20the%20fears%20were%20illogical%2C%20but%20they%20were%20still%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20initially%20declining%20her%20invitation%2C%20I%20thought%20about%20it%20at%20length.%20I%20hadn't%20seen%20my%20mom%20in%20a%20year%20or%20my%20dad%2C%20both%20of%20whom%20live%20in%20America%2C%20in%20three%20years.%20I%20hadn't%20seen%20the%20friends%20that%20would%20be%20at%20the%20wedding%20in%20over%2010%20years.%20Going%20would%20give%20me%20the%20unique%20opportunity%20to%20catch%20up%20with%20all%20of%20them%20in%20one%20fell%20swoop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWith%20some%20planning%2C%20I%20made%20it%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EReopening%20my%20computer%2C%20I%20found%20flights%20were%20half%20the%20price%20if%20I%20flew%20into%20Washington%20DC.%20A%20flight%20departed%20on%20December%2028%20and%20returned%20on%20January%203.%20My%20husband%20was%20off%20work%20for%20the%20Christmas%20holidays%20so%20childcare%20wouldn't%20be%20an%20issue.%20Without%20thinking%20for%20longer%20than%20half%20an%20hour%2C%20I%20booked%20the%20ticket.%20There%20was%20no%20turning%20back.%20No%20talking%20myself%20out%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20weeks%20leading%20up%20to%20my%20travel%2C%20I%20should%20have%20been%20excited%2C%20but%20instead%2C%20I%20felt%20a%20knot%20in%20my%20stomach%20every%20time%20it%20came%20to%20mind.%20Most%20concerning%20was%20the%20fact%20that%20I%20had%20forgotten%20how%20to%20plan%20travel%20as%20my%20husband%20is%20the%20expert%20planner%2C%20and%20I've%20always%20left%20this%20task%20to%20him%20since%20we%20married%2012%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20few%20weeks%2C%20I%20let%20anxiety%20gnaw%20away%20at%20me%20but%20then%20decided%20that%20the%20only%20way%20to%20get%20over%20it%20was%20to%20plan%20every%20step%20of%20my%20trip%20meticulously.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20booked%20a%20return%20bus%20ticket%20to%20the%20airport%2C%20bought%20travel%20insurance%2C%20made%20paper%20copies%20and%20took%20photographs%20of%20all%20my%20tickets%20and%20relevant%20documents%2C%20wrote%20a%20list%20of%20what%20I%20needed%20to%20pack%2C%20made%20note%20of%20important%20phone%20numbers%20and%20addresses%2C%20and%20drafted%20an%20itinerary%20that%20I%20send%20to%20the%20people%20I%20would%20be%20visiting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEverything%20I%20could%20control%2C%20I%20had.%20Anything%20else%20was%20out%20of%20my%20control%20and%20not%20worth%20worrying%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20really%20enjoyed%20traveling%20alone%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20woke%20on%20the%20day%20of%20my%20departure%2C%20my%20adrenaline%20was%20high%2C%20but%20I%20felt%20confident%20I%20had%20done%20all%20I%20could%20to%20prepare%20for%20the%20trip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20on%20the%20bus%20to%20London%2C%20where%20I%20would%20then%20catch%20my%20flight%2C%20all%20the%20butterflies%20went.%20I%20had%20worked%20myself%20up%20for%20months%20about%20the%20trip%2C%20but%20once%20plans%20were%20being%20lived%20out%2C%20I%20felt%20completely%20relaxed%20and%20totally%20enjoyed%20the%20experience%20of%20traveling%20on%20my%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20kids%20in%20tow%2C%20I%20could%20read%20my%20book%20without%20interruption%2C%20sit%20for%20a%20cappuccino%20at%20the%20airport%2C%20go%20through%20security%20only%20managing%20myself%2C%20try%20on%20makeup%20at%20the%20duty-free%20shops%2C%20people%20watch%20while%20waiting%20for%20my%20plane%20to%20board%2C%20and%20choose%20the%20film%20I%20wanted%20to%20watch%20on%20the%20flight%20while%20drinking%20white%20wine.%20Traveling%20alone%20wasn't%20the%20fearful%20feat%20I%20had%20imagined%2C%20but%20an%20absolute%20breeze.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20five%20days%20I%20was%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I%20was%20totally%20free%20sailing%20woman.%20Meals%20or%20bedtimes%20didn't%20bind%20me.%20Didn't%20have%20to%20settle%20arguments.%20Had%20hours%20of%20long%2C%20uninterrupted%20conversations%20with%20family%20and%20friends%20I%20hadn't%20seen%20in%20years.%20Took%20extra%20long%20showers.%20Went%20to%20the%20gym%20when%20I%20woke%20early%20with%20jet%20lag.%20Browsed%20shops%2C%20trying%20on%20clothes%20without%20rushing.%20Ate%20all%20my%20favourite%20foods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDare%20I%20say%2C%20it%20was%20like%20I%20was%20a%20child-free%20woman.%20As%20if%20I%20had%20rewound%20to%20the%20moment%20I%20left%20America%20to%20move%20to%20the%20UK%20to%20get%20married%2012%20years%20ago.%20I%20could%20feel%20myself%20being%20rejuvenated%20by%20having%20so%20few%20responsibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20as%20the%20trip%20came%20to%20an%20end%2C%20I%20was%20ready%20to%20go%20home.%20To%20be%20smothered%20in%20hugs%20and%20kisses%20and%20endlessly%20listen%20to%20whatever%20my%20kids%20wanted%20to%20tell%20me%20about%20what%20they%20did%20while%20I%20was%20away.%20Because%20although%20I%20enjoyed%20the%20stint%20away%20from%20reality%2C%20I%20love%20my%20reality%20%E2%80%94%20the%20day-to-day%20with%20my%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20wasn't%20a%20hint%20of%20anxiety%20about%20travel%20on%20the%20way%20home%20because%20I'd%20already%20proven%20to%20myself%20that%20I%20could%20do%20this.%20There%20was%20nothing%20to%20be%20afraid%20of.%20Proof%20that%20often%2C%20by%20doing%20the%20very%20thing%20I'm%20afraid%20of%2C%20even%20though%20it%20feels%20uncomfortable%2C%20I%20can%20break%20the%20power%20fear%20has%20over%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-solo-travel-freedom-no-kids-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705326241000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F