0Mount%20St.%20Joseph%20University%2C%20and%20creator%20of%20Cicada%20Safari%2C%20an%20app%20that%20crowdsources%20cicada%20photos%20for%20scientific%20research%2C%20is%20excited%20to%20see%20cicadas%20again%20this%20year%20after%20last%20year's%20stragglers.%20He's%20very%20aware%2C%20however%2C%20of%20how%20polarizing%20the%20insect%20can%20be%2C%20both%20on%20and%20offline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20they%20show%20up%20in%20thousands%2C%20make%20a%20lot%20of%20noise%2C%20and%20their%20crushed%20remains%20can%20even%20be%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fohio-man-hits-pole-after-cicada-flies-his-face-driving-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehazard%20to%20drivers%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fextension.purdue.edu%2Fnews%2Fcounty%2Fwhitley%2F2021%2F02%2Fperiodical-cicadas--unhurried-but-reliable-metamorphosis.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emaking%20roads%20slippery%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESometimes%2C%20they%20can%20harm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fsafepestcontrol%2Fcicadas%23%3A~%3Atext%3DCicadas%2520are%2520not%2520harmful%2520to%2Cadult%2520males%2527%2520loud%2520courting%2520sounds.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyoung%20trees%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20attempting%20to%20lay%20their%20eggs%20in%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20cicadas%20are%20harmless%20and%20don't%20hurt%20people%20or%20animals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20helped%20people%20plan%20vacations%20to%20where%20the%20cicadas%20are%20emerging%2C%26quot%3B%20Kritsky%20said.%20%26quot%3BI've%20helped%20people%20plan%20vacations%20to%20be%20outside%20of%20where%20they're%20emerging.%20So%20there's%20both%20extremes%20on%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20annual%20cicadas%2C%20periodical%20cicadas%20spend%20years%20in%20their%20underground%20rooms%20like%20brooding%20teenagers%20(is%20that%20why%20they're%20called%20broods%3F)%20in%2013%20or%2017-year%20cycles.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20the%20next%20two%20emerging%20broods%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F17-year-cicadas-will-overrun-the-east-coast-any-day-now-2013-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrood%20XIII%3C%2Fa%3E%20emerges%20every%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbillions-of-cicadas-are-about-to-take-the-east-coast-by-storm-2016-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E17%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20Brood%20XIX%20emerges%20every%2013%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%2015%20broods%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%2012%20are%2017-year%20broods%2C%20and%20three%20are%2013-year%20broods.%20Kritsky%20said%20this%20means%20there%20have%20been%20other%20instances%20of%20two%20broods%20concurrently%20appearing%20in%20more%20recent%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%201998%2C%20we%20had%20a%2017-year%20brood%20come%20out%20with%20a%2013-year%20brood%2C%26quot%3B%20Kritsky%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20this%20happens.%20It%20happened%20probably%2012%20times%2C%20at%20least%2C%20in%20the%20last%20200%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%2C%20however%2C%20that%20the%20periodical%20cicadas%20%E2%80%94%20which%20emerge%20in%20the%20millions%20%E2%80%94%20aren't%20a%20sight%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20life%20of%20a%20periodical%20cicada%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeriodical%20cicadas%2C%20a%20red-eyed%20insect%20with%20a%20black%20body%20and%20orange%20rings%2C%20spend%20most%20of%20their%20life%20just%20inches%20below%20the%20dirt%2C%20beneath%20trees.%20It%20gets%20a%20bit%20cold%20at%20that%20depth%2C%20around%2056%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%2C%20so%20they%20don't%20move%20around%20much.%20The%20cicada%20nymphs%20tunnel%20around%20and%20live%20off%20of%20the%20sap%20of%20tree%20roots.%20Kritsky%20told%20BI%20that%20many%20live%20near%20parks%20and%20cemeteries%20in%20suburban%20areas%20because%20they%20are%20drawn%20to%20%26quot%3Bmature%20trees%2C%20in%20full%20sun%2C%20with%20low%20vegetation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20their%20life%20for%2013%20to%2017%20years%20until%20it%20is%20time%20to%20reproduce.%20Scientists%20don't%20know%20exactly%20how%20they%20determine%20how%20many%20years%20have%20passed%2C%20but%20evidence%20shows%20that%20they%20keep%20track%20of%20seasons%20by%20detecting%20the%20flow%20of%20sap%20in%20the%20trees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20time%20comes%2C%20they%20emerge%20in%20late%20spring%2C%20when%20soil%20temperatures%20reach%20about%2065%20degrees.%20This%20happens%20at%20different%20times%20in%20different%20locations%20between%20late%20April%20and%20early%20June.%20Depending%20on%20temperatures%2C%20Kritsky%20said%20Brood%20XIII%20could%20appear%20in%20early%20June%20or%20late%20May.%20Brood%20XIX%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20Great%20Southern%20Brood%2C%20could%20appear%20as%20early%20as%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cicadas%20usually%20first%20appear%20at%20night.%20Males%20will%20make%20their%20way%20out%20for%20the%20first%20couple%20of%20days%2C%20climbing%20up%20trees%2C%20and%20females%20will%20later%20follow.%20The%20first%20days%20of%20freedom%20are%20about%20shedding%20their%20old%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmilitary-exoskeletons-2014-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexoskeleton%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20hardening%20their%20new%20exoskeleton%20to%20become%20fully%20grown%20adults.%20Then%20it's%20time%20to%20mate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20attract%20a%20mate%2C%20male%20cicadas%20use%20an%20organ%20in%20their%20body%20that%20creates%20a%20sound%20similar%20to%20a%20shrieking%20buzz.%20This%20may%20be%20what%20people%20recognize%20most%20about%20cicadas%20because%20they%20can%20get%20loud%20%E2%80%94%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.cdc.gov%2Fniosh-science-blog%2F2021%2F07%2F20%2Fnoise-myths-cicada%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erunning%20lawnmower%3C%2Fa%3E%20loud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FzFmvl_aVEx8%3Fsi%3DIo4GIHXEoRzdu916%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20female%20is%20into%20the%20call%2C%20they%20mate.%20The%20female%20then%20searches%20for%20trees%20in%20brighter%20areas%2C%20locates%20tiny%20twigs%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20branches%2C%20cuts%20into%20them%2C%20and%20lays%20between%20400-600%20eggs.%20If%20they%20run%20out%20of%20room%20on%20one%20twig%2C%20they'll%20fly%20to%20another%2C%20Kritsky%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20they%20complete%20their%20mission%2C%20adult%20cicadas%20soon%20die.%20In%20about%20six%20weeks%2C%20the%20eggs%20hatch%20from%20the%20trees%2C%20fall%20to%20the%20ground%2C%20and%20burrow%20into%20the%20earth%20to%20start%20the%20cycle%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECrowdsourcing%20has%20changed%20the%20cicada%20game%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20Cicada%20Safari's%20existence%2C%20Kritsky%20said%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20records%20on%20cicadas%20was%20about%208%2C000%20records%20of%20cicada%20locations.%20His%20research%20teams%20have%20received%20over%20half%20a%20million%20records%20since%202019%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20thousands%20of%20cicada%20enthusiasts%20submitting%20photos.%20Kritsky%20said%20it's%20helped%20cicada%20scientists%20understand%20the%20distribution%20of%20periodical%20cicadas%20more%20precisely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20found%20records%20from%20areas%20where%20cicadas%20never%20got%20reported%20before%2C%20not%20because%20they%20weren't%20there%2C%20but%20no%20one%20knew%20who%20to%20report%20it%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20Kritsky%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20app%20has%20also%20helped%20researchers%20spot%20new%20patterns%20of%20emergence.%20Smaller%20swaths%20of%20periodical%20cicadas%20no