html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Foyo-plans-400-properties-at-spiritual-places-including-ayodhya-in-2024-124011500538_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Africa%E2%80%99s%20Crises%20Fall%20Out%20of%20Focus%20as%20Global%20Attention%20Drifts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F15164502%2Fimage-1745.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ECrises%20in%20Africa%20are%20being%20overlooked%2C%20with%20news%20about%20humanitarian%20emergencies%20on%20the%20continent%20buried%20beneath%20the%20weight%20of%20media%20attention%20focused%20elsewhere%2C%20Care%20International%E2%80%99s%202023%20report%20concludes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20issues%20such%20as%20hunger%20in%20Angola%2C%20chronic%20malnutrition%20in%20Burundi%20and%20high%20child%20mortality%20in%20the%20Central%20African%20Republic%20are%20disappearing%20from%20public%20view%2C%20the%20authors%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnalyst%20Fredson%20Guilengue%20from%20the%20Rosa%20Luxemburg%20Foundation%20in%20Johannesburg%20sees%20reasons%20for%20the%20low%20interest%20in%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20plight%20in%20the%20escalation%20of%20the%20two%20conflicts%20in%20the%20West.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20first%20is%20the%20continuation%20of%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war.%20It%20is%20getting%20a%20lot%20of%20attention%20worldwide%2C%20especially%20on%20the%20European%20continent%2C%20because%20the%20war%20is%20returning%20to%20Europe%2C%E2%80%9D%20Guilengue%20told%20%3Cem%3EDW.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20global%20media%20is%20now%20focusing%20more%20on%20Europe%20and%20less%20on%20Africa%20or%20other%20places.%20This%20will%20continue%20in%202024%20as%20the%20wars%20continue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20second%20trouble%20spot%2C%20namely%20the%20conflict%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%20in%20Gaza%2C%20has%20exacerbated%20this%20dilemma%3A%20what%20is%20happening%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20hardly%20receives%20any%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20current%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.care.de%2Fschwerpunkte%2Fnothilfe%2Fvergessene-krisen%2F%5C%22%3E%20%E2%80%9CBreaking%20the%20Silence%E2%80%9D%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20aid%20organisation%20draws%20attention%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cforgotten%20crises%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20eighth%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20year%2C%20Care%20lists%20the%20ten%20humanitarian%20emergencies%20in%20the%20world%20that%20have%20hardly%20been%20reported.%20In%202023%20and%202022%2C%20they%20all%20took%20place%20in%20Africa%2C%20led%20in%20the%20second%20year%20by%20Angola.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Central%20African%20Republic%20occupied%20a%20place%20in%20this%20sad%20list%20every%20year%2C%20emphasised%20David%20Mutua%2C%20Care%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20African%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAngola%20in%20extreme%20distress%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aid%20organisation%20commissioned%20the%20media%20monitoring%20service%20Meltwater%20to%20examine%20five%20million%20online%20articles%20in%20Arabic%2C%20German%2C%20English%2C%20French%20and%20Spanish%20from%20January%201%20to%20September%2030%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20list%20of%2048%20humanitarian%20crises%20affecting%20more%20than%20one%20million%20people%20the%20ten%20crises%20with%20the%20lowest%20media%20presence%20were%20identified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%2077%2C000%20of%20the%20articles%20analyzed%20dealt%20with%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20humanitarian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fworld-bank-extreme-poverty-here-to-stay%2Fa-63346922%5C%22%3Edisasters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20new%20Barbie%20film%2C%20which%20topped%20the%20list%20with%20273%2C279%20publications%2C%20Care%20Africa%20spokesperson%20Mutua%20said%20at%20the%20presentation%20of%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAngola%20accounted%20for%20just%20under%201%2C000%20publications%2C%20although%20drought%2C%20flooding%20and%20hunger%20meant%20that%20more%20than%20seven%20million%20people%20needed%20humanitarian%20aid%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAngolans%20have%20been%20struggling%20with%20drought%20for%2040%20years%2C%20there%20is%20a%20lack%20of%20clean%20drinking%20water%20and%20almost%20thirty%20years%20of%20civil%20war%20(1975%20to%202002)%20have%20left%20a%20country%20littered%20with%20mines.%20Although%20it%20is%20rich%20in%20oil%20and%20diamonds%2C%20most%20of%20the%20approximately%2037%20million%20Angolans%20live%20in%20poverty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EClimate%20change%20drives%20crises%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20second%20place%20is%20Zambia%2C%20where%201.35%20million%20people%20are%20affected%20by%20hunger.%20The%20country%20is%20suffering%20greatly%20from%20the%20consequences%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fel-nino-2023-on-track-to-be-hottest-year-ever-on-record%2Fa-66504033%5C%22%3Eclimate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20too%2C%20is%20Burundi%20where%20the%20population%20regularly%20battles%20floods.%20Almost%2070%2C000%20people%20have%20been%20displaced%20as%20a%20result%2C%20and%20almost%205.6%20million%20children%20in%20the%20small%20East%20African%20country%20are%20chronically%20malnourished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20many%20people%20in%20Senegal%20and%20Mauritania%20also%20also%20suffer%20from%20hunger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20impact%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fclimate-change-exacerbating-conflict-and-poverty-imf%2Fa-66668775%5C%22%3Eclimate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20people%20and%20food%20security%20is%20serious%20and%20largely%20avoidable.%20%E2%80%9CClimate%20change%20drives%20famine%2C%20it%20makes%20water%20problems%20worse%2C%20it%20destroys%20people%E2%80%99s%20habitats%20and%20drives%20them%20out%20of%20their%20homes%2C%20it%20prevents%20children%20from%20going%20to%20school%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Deepmala%20Mahla%2C%20Care%E2%80%99s%20Director%20for%20Humanitarian%20Aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20consequences%20are%20dramatic.%20One%20Somali%20woman%20in%20Kenya%20told%20Mahla%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20climate%2C%20the%20drought%20and%20the%20weapons%20haven%E2%80%99t%20killed%20me%2C%20but%20I%20feel%20dead%20inside.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20almost%20300%20million%20people%20worldwide%20will%20need%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fafrica-imf-sounds-alarm-on-declining-aid-rising-debt%2Fa-65330477%5C%22%3Ehumanitarian%20aid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Care%20International%20warned%2C%20almost%20half%20of%20them%20in%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDavid%20Mutua%20cites%20climate%20change%20as%20a%20decisive%20factor.%20From%20devastating%20droughts%20to%20extreme%20flooding%20%E2%80%94%20the%20continent%20suffers%20the%20most%20from%20climate%20change%2C%20even%20though%20it%20contributes%20the%20least%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorldwide%2C%20humanitarian%20need%20has%20never%20been%20greater%20than%20in%202023.%20For%20Mahla%2C%20it%20is%20therefore%20not%20surprising%20that%20disasters%20in%20Africa%20receive%20too%20little%20attention%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20experienced%20an%20unprecedented%20series%20of%20humanitarian%20crises%20and%20natural%20disasters%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20earthquake%20in%20the%20Syrian-Turkish%20border%20region%2C%20floods%20in%20Libya%2C%20but%20also%20the%20wars%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECrises%20escalate%20in%20the%20shadow%20of%20crises%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20humanitarian%20crises%20in%20Africa%20would%20not%20make%20it%20into%20the%20news%20because%20they%20are%20all%20too%20familiar.%20They%20%E2%80%9Calready%20exist%2C%20sometimes%20they%20escalate%20in%20the%20shadow%20of%20the%20major%20crises%2C%E2%80%9D%20added%20Mahla.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20nothing%20new%20to%20report%2C%20as%20sad%20as%20that%20sounds.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Fred%20Guilengue%2C%20fatigue%20over%20the%20numerous%20crises%20in%20Africa%20is%20a%20factor%20that%20inhibits%20attention%3A%20%E2%80%9CBut%20this%20tiredness%20has%20not%20just%20set%20in%20now%2C%20it%20already%20existed%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%201990s%20and%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%202000s.%20Western%20countries%20were%20already%20tired%20of%20not%20seeing%20results%20when%20it%20came%20to%20democracy%20on%20the%20African%20continent%20and%20foreign%20aid%20in%20particular%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20emphasised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20Deepmala%20Mahla%20notes%20that%20reporting%20from%20Africa%20is%20very%20expensive%20for%20foreign%20journalists%20and%20media%20groups.%20Many%20of%20these%20humanitarian%20crises%20are%20located%20in%20insecure%20regions%20that%20are%20subject%20to%20numerous%20restrictions%20imposed%20by%20governments%2C%20limiting%20access%20to%20these%20areas%20for%20journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20example%20is%20the%20Central%20African%20Republic.%20An%20armed%20conflict%20has%20been%20raging%20there%20since%202013%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwhich%20has%20repeatedly%20escalated%20and%20displaced%20families%20several%20times%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Deepmala%20Mahla%20from%20Care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwenty%20percent%20of%20the%20population%20have%20been%20internally%20displaced%20or%20have%20fled%20to%20neighbouring%20countries.%20%E2%80%9CTwo-thirds%20of%20the%20population%2C%20more%20than%20three%20million%20people%2C%20have%20been%20in%20need%20of%20humanitarian%20aid%20for%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20criticizes%20Mahla.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople%20are%20tired%20of%20crises%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Care%20International%2C%20there%20is%20also%20a%20lack%20of%20sufficient%20funding%20for%20humanitarian%20aid%20to%20save%20lives.%20In%202023%2C%20only%2035%25%20of%20the%20required%20financial%20resources%20were%20provided%20by%20donors.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20also%20aware%20that%20people%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20or%20can%E2%80%99t%20consume%20news%20about%20disasters%20all%20the%20time%2C%20people%20are%20tired%20of%20crises%2C%E2%80%9D%20emphasised%20Mahla.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetter%20cooperation%20with%20the%20media%20and%20politicians%20is%20necessary%20to%20bring%20such%20emergencies%20to%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20global%20public%2C%20she%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fafricas-crises-fall-out-of-focus-as-global-attention-drifts%2Fa-67965128%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EDW.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705317742000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F15164502%2Fimage-1745.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fafricas-crises-fall-out-of-focus-as-global-attention-drifts%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Care%20International%20has%20listed%20the%20ten%20forgotten%20humanitarian%20crises%20of%20last%20year%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20them%20in%20Africa.%20Climate%20change%20plays%20a%20huge%20role%2C%20the%20aid%20organisation%20says%2C%20and%20more%20media%20attention%20is%20needed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fafricas-crises-fall-out-of-focus-as-global-attention-drifts%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'I%20wasn't%20the%20last%20left-hander...'%3A%20England%20batter%20on%20his%20struggle%20vs%20Ashwin%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705317583000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106866212%2Cimgsize-45540.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fengland-in-india%2Fi-wasnt-the-last-left-hander-england-batter-on-his-struggle-against-world-class-ashwin%2Farticleshow%2F106866266.cms%22%2C%22summary