%20early%201970s%2C%20led%20a%20one-man%20crusade%20to%20reform%20contemporary%20Muslim%20society.%20He%20sharply%20criticised%20the%20community%20for%20its%20backwardness%20and%20hoped%20that%20the%20spirit%20of%20critical%20introspection%20would%20suffuse%20Indian%20Muslims%20and%20strengthen%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20secular%20and%20national%20order%20and%20defuse%20the%20nascent%20Hindu%20chauvinism.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20262px)%2085vw%2C%20262px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F15152821%2FScreenshot-2024-01-15-at-3.28.13-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22262%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F15152821%2FScreenshot-2024-01-15-at-3.28.13-PM.png%20748w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F15152821%2FScreenshot-2024-01-15-at-3.28.13-PM-187x300.png%20187w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F15152821%2FScreenshot-2024-01-15-at-3.28.13-PM-638x1024.png%20638w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-693017%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22420%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHamid%20Dalwai%2C%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EMuslim%20Politics%20in%20India%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EPenguin%20Random%20House%20(2023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDalwai%E2%80%99s%20presence%20in%20Indian%20affairs%20(though%20largely%20confined%20to%20Maharashtra)%20was%20comet-like.%20Born%20in%201932%2C%20he%20passed%20away%20in%201977%2C%20at%20the%20age%20of%2044%20years.%20His%20writings%20have%20had%20a%20chequered%20history.%20A%20few%20articles%20by%20him%20were%20published%20in%201968%3B%20a%20slightly%20larger%20collection%20came%20out%20in%201972.%20The%20additional%20material%20in%20the%20latter%20was%20largely%20derived%20from%20conversations%20Dalwai%20had%20with%20the%20Marathi%20poet%20and%20critic%2C%20Dilip%20Chitre%2C%20which%20the%20latter%20transcribed%20and%20then%20rendered%20into%20English.%20Thus%2C%20the%20text%20in%20this%20book%20is%20over%2050%20years%20old.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%20an%20early%20age%2C%20Dalwai%20was%20a%20social%20reformer.%20He%20joined%20the%20Socialist%20Party%2C%20but%20disagreed%20with%20it%20strongly%20for%20its%20failure%20to%20%E2%80%9Ctake%20up%20a%20clear%2C%20hard%20line%20on%20Muslim%20communalism%E2%80%9D.%20Dalwai%20frequently%20denied%20he%20was%20an%20intellectual%20or%20an%20academic%2C%20making%20up%20in%20fervour%20what%20he%20lacked%20in%20learning.%20His%20short%20foray%20in%20public%20life%20was%20consistently%20controversial%20as%20he%20asserted%20his%20views%20on%20Muslim%20obscurantism%20with%20vigour%20and%20self-confidence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDalwai%E2%80%99s%20thinking%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDalwai%E2%80%99s%20views%20were%20simple%20and%20clear.%20Indian%20Muslims%20were%20clinging%20to%20outdated%20traditions%20and%20had%20failed%20to%20obtain%20modern%20education.%20They%2C%20thus%2C%20had%20failed%20to%20integrate%20with%20the%20broad%20stream%20of%20national%20life%3B%20they%20in%20fact%20saw%20the%20Hindu%20and%20Muslim%20communities%20as%20autonomous%20and%20parallel%20societies.%20Hindus%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20had%20opted%20for%20modern%20education%2C%20with%20leaders%20like%20Raja%20Ram%20Mohan%20Roy%2C%20and%20had%2C%20over%20time%2C%20developed%20a%20healthy%20liberal%20humanist%20tradition.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20Muslim%20separateness%20and%20obduracy%20that%20had%20led%20to%20Partition%2C%20with%20Muslim%20leaders%20conniving%20with%20British%20officials%20to%20obtain%20the%20vivisection%20of%20the%20country.%20But%20Partition%20was%20only%20the%20first%20step%20in%20the%20Muslim%20agenda%3A%20their%20ultimate%20goal%20was%20to%20make%20the%20entire%20sub-continent%20Muslim.%20Hindu%20communalism%20was%20never%20very%20strong%20and%20was%20entirely%20a%20response%20to%20Muslim%20communalism.%20In%20any%20case%2C%20Hindu%20obscurantism%20was%20tempered%20by%20its%20liberals%2C%20however%20few%20they%20might%20be%2C%20but%20the%20Muslims%20had%20no-one%20to%20moderate%20their%20beliefs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20root%20cause%20of%20the%20Muslim%20malaise%2C%20Dalwai%20believed%2C%20was%20Islam%20itself%3A%20Muslims%20believed%20that%20theirs%20was%20the%20perfect%20faith%2C%20and%20hence%20they%20clung%20to%20its%20medieval%20and%20obsolete%20traditions.%20In%20fact%2C%20Muslim%20backwardness%20was%20inherent%20in%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20make-up%20of%20the%20Muslim%20mind%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20could%20be%20traced%20to%20their%20conviction%20that%20theirs%20was%20a%20perfect%20society%20and%20they%20were%20%E2%80%9Csuperior%20to%20all%20other%20communities%20in%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Frare-interview-of-hamid-dalwai-gives-insight-into-the-social-reformers-thinking%5C%22%3ERare%20Interview%20of%20Hamid%20Dalwai%20Gives%20Insight%20Into%20the%20Social%20Reformer%E2%80%99s%20Thinking%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDalwai%20deeply%20disliked%20most%20contemporary%20Muslim%20movements%20and%20organisations%2C%20blaming%20them%20for%20keeping%20the%20community%20backward.%20Thus%2C%20he%20asserted%20that%20the%20seminary%20at%20Deoband%20had%20forced%20Muslims%20to%20reject%20modern%20education%3B%20that%20the%20Jamaat-e-Islami%2C%20described%20as%20%E2%80%9Can%20anti-Hindu%20Wahhabi%20organization%E2%80%9D%2C%20was%20the%20dominant%20influence%20on%20Muslims%20all%20across%20north%20India%3B%20and%20the%20Jamiat-Ulema-e-Hind%2C%20earlier%20associated%20with%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20freedom%20movement%2C%20%E2%80%9Cgradually%20adopted%20an%20obscurantist%20and%20communal%20posture%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EEnigmatic%20personality%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHalf%20a%20century%20later%2C%20Dalwai%20remains%20an%20enigmatic%20figure.%20His%20forceful%20pronouncements%20date%20back%20to%20the%20early%201970s%2C%20a%20decade%20before%20the%20Vishwa%20Hindu%20Parishad%20took%20up%20the%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi%20movement%20and%20heralded%20the%20inauguration%20of%20the%20nationwide%20Hindutva%20project.%20But%2C%20despite%20this%2C%20it%20is%20surprising%20that%20he%20completely%20missed%20the%20powerful%20and%20influential%20presence%20of%20Hindu%20nationalism%2C%20as%20exemplified%20by%20the%20RSS%2C%20headquartered%20at%20Nagpur%2C%20and%20the%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%2C%20at%20one%20time%20led%20by%20Veer%20Savarkar%2C%20in%20Mumbai.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15112516%2Fimg_2622-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15112516%2Fimg_2622-2.jpg%201080w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15112516%2Fimg_2622-2-300x120.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15112516%2Fimg_2622-2-1024x410.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668157%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22432%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20shows%20no%20knowledge%20of%20assertions%20of%20a%20separate%20Hindu%20identity%20that%20had%20been%20shaped%20over%20the%20previous%20century%20by%20Swami%20Dayanand%20Saraswati%20and%20his%20Arya%20Sabha%20movement%2C%20and%20the%20substantial%20ideological%20contributions%20of%20ideologues%20such%20as%20Savarkar%2C%20Golwarkar%20and%20Hedgewar.%20Their%20writings%20viewed%20Hindu%20identity%20as%20having%20distinct%20cultural%20and%20ethnic%20moorings%20and%20saw%20the%20Muslim%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9COther%E2%80%9D.%20As%20early%20as%201909%2C%20Lala%20Lajpat%20Rai%20had%20described%20the%20Hindus%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnation%20in%20themselves%2C%20because%20they%20represent%20a%20type%20of%20civilisation%20all%20their%20own%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20if%20we%20were%20to%20excuse%20Dalwai%E2%80%99s%20lack%20of%20knowledge%20about%20the%20century-old%20wellsprings%20of%20Hindu%20nationalism%20in%20India%20on%20account%20of%20his%20lack%20of%20formal%20education%2C%20it%20is%20astonishing%20that%20Dalwai%20makes%20only%20a%20fleeting%20reference%20to%20the%20communal%20riots%20in%20Bhiwandi%20and%20neighbouring%20towns%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20May%201970.%20The%20riots%20caused%20the%20deaths%20of%20over%20250%20people.%20The%20Justice%20Madon%20commission%2C%20which%20investigated%20the%20riots%2C%20stated%20that%20142%20Muslims%20and%2020%20Hindus%20had%20been%20killed%20in%20Bhiwandi%20alone.%C2%A0The%20enquiry%20commission%20criticiseded%20the%20police%20for%20anti-Muslim%20bias%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20violence%2C%20and%20also%20criticised%20the%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EShiv%20Sena%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20then%20in%20its%20early%20days%2C%20for%20its%20role%20in%20the%20riots.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ELimited%20intellectual%20foundations%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDalwai%20spouted%20his%20self-assured%20views%20on%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20subjects%2C%20but%20on%20most%20of%20them%20he%20was%20ill-informed%20%E2%80%93%20obviously%2C%20he%20had%20little%20knowledge%20of%20Islam%20the%20faith%3B%20Muslim%20history%3B%20debates%20in%20India%20in%20the%2019%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20early%2020%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20centuries%20on%20the%20shape%20of%20the%20national%20order%20after%20independence%3B%20communal%20politics%20that%20led%20to%20Partition%2C%20or%20even%20the%20wellsprings%20of%20communalism%20in%20India%20after%20independence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHis%20uni-focal%20lens%2C%20pointed%20at%20Muslim%20follies%20and%20shortcomings%2C%20blinded%20him%20to%20the%20broader%20national%20scenario%20in%20which%20large%20sections%20of%20the%20majority%20community%20solely%20blamed%20Muslims%20for%20Partition%2C%20rejected%20the%20national%20secular%20order%2C%20engineered%20communal%20riots%20regularly%20to%20cow%20down%20Muslim%20minorities%2C%20and%2C%20over%20time%2C%20had%20sought%20to%20marginalise%20Muslims%20in%20the%20national%20political%2C%20economic%20and%20social%20order.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20his%20active%20period%2C%20Dalwai%20was%20vilified%20by%20Muslims%20for%20his%20one-sided%20castigation%20of%20the%20Muslim%2C%20with%20few%20and%20feeble%20references%20to%20Hindu%20communalism.%20Many%20then%20thought%20he%20was%20the%20mouthpiece%20of%20Hindu%20extremist%20groups.%20This%20might%20not%20have%20been%20the%20case%3B%20while%20today%2C%20a%20decade%20of%20Modi-raj%20has%20encouraged%20some%20Muslims%20to%20join%20the%20Hindutva%20bandwagon%2C%20largely%20for%20personal%20advantage%2C%2050%20years%20ago%20this%20was%20unusual%20%E2%80%93%20most%20Muslims%2C%20liberal%20and%20traditional%2C%20basked%20in%20the%20national%20secular%20order%20that%20gave%20them%20security%2C%20opportunity%20and%20dignity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EExplaining%20this%20publication%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20likely%20that%20Dalwai%20was%20a%20stand-alone%20maverick%20who%20truly%20believed%20what%20he%20said%20and%20desperately%20wanted%20his%20community%20to%20shed%20its%20obscurantism%2C%20become%20introspective%20about%20its%20shortcomings%2C%20and%20grasp%20the%20values%20of%20liberalism%20and%20secularism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20more%20interesting%20area%20of%20enquiry%20is%3A%20why%20has%20a%20leading%20publishing%20house%2C%20Penguin%20Random%20House%2C%20felt%20the%20need%20to%20reprint%20the%2050-year%20old%20fulminations%20of%20this%20obscure%20activist%20who%20made%20hardly%20any%20mark%20in%20his%20short%20life%20and%20remains%20unremembered%20over%20the%20last%20several%20decades.%20(Notably%2C%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Csecular%E2%80%9D%20before%20%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%9D%20has%20been%20removed%20from%20the%20publication%20of%201972.)%20It%20is%20again%20surprising%20that%20this%20reprint%20has%20no%20fresh%20%E2%80%98Foreword%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98Introduction%E2%80%99%20that%20would%20place%20the%20publication%20in%20a%20contemporary%20context%20and%20explain%20the%20need%20to%20revisit%20Dalwai%E2%80%99s%20writings%20after%20five%20decades.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDalwai%E2%80%99s%20thinking%20on%20most%20matters%20that%20he%20agitated%20in%20public%20was%20puerile%2C%20crude%20and%20rudimentary.%20The%20issues%20he%20addressed%2C%20particularly%20those%20pertaining%20to%20Muslim%20politics%2C%20Partition%2C%20communalism%20in%20India%2C%20and%20Hindu%20nationalism%2C%20have%20over%20the%20years%20been%20explored%20in%20depth%20by%20several%20far%20better%20scholars%2C%20exposing%20most%20of%20his%20observations%20as%20both%20uninformed%20and%20cringe-worthy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20only%20explanation%20for%20this%20publication%20that%20makes%20sense%20is%20that%20Dalwai%E2%80%99s%20simplistic%20views%20are%20fully%20in%20accord%20with%20the%20foundational%20thinking%20of%20present-day%20Hindutva%20acolytes.%20You%20can%E2%80%99t%20do%20better%20than%20restate%20them%20through%20the%20five-decade%20old%20writings%20of%20a%20Muslim%2C%20however%20shallow%20and%20ignorant%20he%20might%20have%20been.%20Surprisingly%2C%20Penguin%20have%20m